getValidationGroup

java.lang.String getValidationGroup()
                                    throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Returns the name of the validation group. The validation group name indicates which attributes of a user-defined type are grouped together as part of the same validation unit. This allows the attributes assigned to a user-defined type to be mapped to the same columns of a valid set, yet be grouped into separate validation units. Note that this field is only valid if the valid set is comprised of more than one column.

Returns:
the validation group name.
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

setValidSet

void setValidSet(ValidSet validSet)
                 throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Assigns, or deassigns, this attribute to, or from, a single-column valid set.

If validSet is not null, this method assigns this attribute to column 1 of the validSet. An exception will be raised if this attribute and validSet are defined in different products.

If validSet is null, this method deassigns this attribute from the valid set it is currently assigned to. If validSet is not a single-column valid set, an exception will be raised.

Parameters:
validSet - the valid set to assign or deassign, to or from, this attribute.
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

assignValidSet

void assignValidSet(ValidSet validSet,
                    java.lang.String validationGroup,
                    int columnNumber,
                    boolean autoPopulate)
                    throws DimensionsRuntimeException
Assigns the specified (multi-column) valid set to this attribute.

Parameters:
validSet - the valid set to assign to this attribute. An exception will be raised if attribute and this valid set are defined in different products
validationGroup - the name of the validation group. Validation groups are used to indicate which attributes of this attribute's parent type are grouped together as part of the same validation unit.
columnNumber - valid set column number
autoPopulate - whether to automatically populate the attribute if a single match against the valid set is found.
Throws:
DimensionsRuntimeException - if connection error or internal error occurs

                        throws DimensionsRuntimeException

Note that attribute rules are not supported for user object types.

Returns:
an unmodifiable list of this attribute's rules.
Throws:
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - if this attribute is defined in a user object type.
